    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Jamiel Shaw, II Memorial Act of 2017</b></p> <p> This bill prohibits the payment of funds to a state or its political subdivisions&nbsp;under any program or activity administered by the Department of Homeland Security&nbsp;unless such state: (1)&nbsp;compiles statistics on each person arrested, charged, convicted of a crime, or incarcerated by such state, including the immigration status and country of origin of such persons and the crimes for which such persons were arrested, charged,&nbsp;convicted, or incarcerated; (2) reports such statistics monthly to the Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI); and (3) certifies, on a monthly basis, compliance with the requirements of this bill.&nbsp;Each federal agency must compile similar statistics and report on such statistics monthly to the FBI.</p> <p>The FBI must annually publish all statistics reported under this bill as a separate data collection of&nbsp;its Uniform Crime Reports. </p>]]></text>
